article.headline: E. Illinois 71, Tennessee St. 61
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. -- Ousmane Cisse had 22 points and 10 rebounds to lead Eastern Illinois to a 71-61 win over Tennessee State on Thursday night. Tyler Laser scored 15 points and T.J. Marion added 12 points for Eastern Illinois (2-4, 1-0 Ohio Valley), which led 37-26 at halftime. Tennessee State (2-4, 1-0) had a 6-0 run late in the second half and pulled to 58-55 with 3:55 left, but the Tigers weren't able to close the gap. Dewayne Wright Jr. and Laser each hit free throws in the final 30 seconds to clinch the win. The Panthers outmuscled the Tigers on offense, with 34 points in the paint, compared to 24 for Tennessee State. Gerald Robinson led Tennessee State with 14 points. Darius Cox and Stephen Evans each added 13 points, and Jerrell Houston had 11 rebounds.
